  "notes": "ANTI-OVERCLAIM: this packet proves only bounded companion infrastructure, not Erdos #1052 itself (genuinely OPEN) and not the full known Subbarao-Warren 1966 companion result (unitary perfect numbers are even) -- that headline theorem still additionally needs filter_not_dvd_eq_uDiv_ordCompl, sum_uDiv_factor (a Finset.sum_bij' 5-argument bijection with deeply nested bullets), and sum_uDiv_even (a Finset.sum_involution 4-argument involution), all deferred to a future cycle. Proof authority: Lean kernel via the tracked proof-search loop (episode 2d9c2f64, problem_version ac4911a9-a44e-47a0-8a4f-d1df1330bdd9), submitted as a SubmitModule (1 def uDiv + 2 helper theorems mem_uDiv/ordProj_dvd_of_mem_uDiv + root theorem not_dvd_div_ordProj), kernel_verified on the FIRST attempt -- unlike the prior erdos_1052_proper_eq_erase packet, none of these three lemmas needed bullet-free rewriting (the sibling source already had no `.`-bullet case splits in them), so this was a near-verbatim transport with only the standard `have h := by tac1; tac2` -> `have h := (by tac1; tac2)` parenthesization fix applied once (in ordProj_dvd_of_mem_uDiv's `happ`) per the documented flattened-sequence lesson. Independently re-verified in THIS environment's own pinned toolchain rather than treated as evidence merely because the sibling repo already reports it kernel_verified there -- per this repo's evidence policy. training.eligibility: quarantined per the default-quarantine policy for open_problem_related packets pending real external review.",
